>> source: https://thevanillabeanblog.com/cinnamon-rolls/
>> time required: 15 hours
>> serves: 12
>> tags: breakfast, bake-off

To make the dough: In a #bowl{} or the bowl of a #stand mixer{}, whisk together the warm @whole milk{3/4%cup}, @honey{1/4%cup}, and @large eggs{4}.

Add the @all-purpose flour{4%cups}, @instant yeast{2 1/4%tsp}, and @salt{2%tsp}. Using a #paddle attachment{}, mix on low speed for 2 minutes until a shaggy dough forms.

Let the dough rest for 15 to ~{20%minutes}.

Switch to a #dough hook{}. Knead the dough on medium-low speed for 5 minutes.

With the mixer running, add the @unsalted butter{10%Tbsp} (at room temperature, cut into 1-inch pieces) one piece at a time, mixing until fully incorporated. Knead for another 5 minutes until the dough is smooth, soft, and slightly sticky.

Place the dough in a #greased bowl{} and cover. Let rise for 30 minutes.

Reach under the dough, pull it up, and fold it over itself. Repeat this folding technique 3 more times at 30-minute intervals (for 2 hours total of rising and folding).

Cover the bowl tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight (or up to 24 hours).

To assemble: Roll the chilled dough on a well-floured surface into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.

Brush the dough with melted @unsalted butter{2%Tbsp} for the filling.

In a small #bowl{}, mix together the @brown sugar{1/2%cup}, @ground cinnamon{1%Tbsp}, and @salt{1%pinch}. Sprinkle this mixture evenly over the butter, pressing down gently.

From the long end, roll the dough into a tight log, pinching the seam to seal.

Cut the log into 12 even rolls using unscented dental floss or a very sharp knife. Place the rolls in a greased #9x13-inch baking pan{} lined with parchment paper.

Cover loosely and let rise in a warm place for 1 to ~{1.5%hours} until puffed and doubled.

Preheat oven to 350°F. Bake the rolls for 25 to ~{30%minutes} until golden brown.

To make the frosting: In a #stand mixer{} fitted with the paddle attachment, beat the @unsalted butter{8%Tbsp} and @cream cheese{4%oz} until smooth. Beat in the @vanilla extract{1%tsp}, @confectioners' sugar{1%cup}, and @salt{1%pinch} until light and fluffy.

Double-glaze: Spread half of the frosting immediately over the warm cinnamon rolls so it melts into the cracks. Allow the rolls to cool for 15 minutes, then spread the remaining frosting over the top.
